{{nihongo|'''Daishi'''|大師|}} is a [[Japanese language|Japanese]] word which means great and/or silent master.  It was also used as an honorary title given by the Japanese Imperial Court.  The closest English translation for the word in this case would be a "great teacher."  Two well known recipients are [[Kukai|Kūkai]] (or Kōbō Daishi) and [[Saicho|Saichō]] (or Dengyō Daishi), the founders of the [[Shingon Buddhism|Shingon]] and [[Tendai]] [[Buddhism|Buddhist]] sects, respectively.  


